pokedexEntries.red: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
pokedexEntries.blue: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Its tongue spans almost 7 feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.
pokedexEntries.gold: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip, so it can be deftly manipulated.
pokedexEntries.silver: Its long tongue, slathered with a thick gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It has a tongue that is over 6'6" long. It uses this long tongue to lick its body clean.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Whenever it sees something unfamiliar, it always licks the object because it memorizes things by texture and taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
pokedexEntries.pearl: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
pokedexEntries.platinum: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip, so it can be deftly manipulated.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
pokedexEntries.black: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.
pokedexEntries.white: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.
pokedexEntries.black2: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.
pokedexEntries.white2: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.
pokedexEntries.x: Its long tongue, slathered in a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
pokedexEntries.y: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It checks out whatever’s around it by licking everything. If you don’t clean off a spot where it’s licked you, you’ll break out in a rash!
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it’s really clean is...questionable.
